translated: Danielsson, Daniel Ragnar, landsfiskal (a type of senior police officer with specific legal duties), Kungsbacka, born on June 20th, 1888 in Ullasjö, Älvsborgs län, son of farmer Josef D. and Nelly Peterson. Married in 1919 to Hanna Persson and they had a son named Åke, born in 1920. Danielsson has held the position of Landsfiskal in Kungsbacka district since 1941. He has been a member of the city council (h) since 1922, chairman of the finance committee since 1937, in the sobriety commission, in the board of directors for A-B Gbgs Banks branch office in Kungsbacka, in the county branch of the Association of Swedish landsfiskaler, and in the tax commission. He has also been a member of the county appeals court from 1928 to 1942 and of the Fjärebygdens road committee among others.
